-- China’s ICBC to Open Second Japan Branch in Osaka, Nikkei Says
-- B y   A d a m   L e
-- 2010-11-16T01:04:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-16/china-s-icbc-to-open-second-japan-branch-in-osaka-nikkei-says.html
Industrial & Commercial Bank of
China Ltd.  will open its second branch in Japan in Osaka this
week, 13 years after opening its first outlet in Tokyo, the
Nikkei newspaper reported.  The seven-person office on Osaka’s Midosuji boulevard will
seek business from the large number of small-to-medium sized
companies in western Japan that deal with China, the  report  said.
ICBC, based in Beijing, is the world’s largest bank by market
value.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Adam Le  in Osaka at 
 ale14@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Drew Gibson in Osaka at 
 dgibson2@bloomberg.net . 